quran[5]{c,v,t,f}:
  5,109,"On the day when Allah gathers the messengers, then says, “What response were you given?” They said{1}, “We have no knowledge; indeed, it is You Who are the Superb Knower of the hidden realms.”",1:[Frequently the Qur’an addresses the events of the Hereafter in pasttense; this grammatical shift should be pondered by the reader.]
  5,110,"When Allah said, “O Jesus, son of Mary, recall My blessing upon you and upon your mother when I aided you with the holy spirit,<i>(making) </i>you speak to people while in the cradle and in the prime of manhood; and when I taught you the Scripture and wisdom and the Torah and the Gospel; and when you create{1}from clay the shape of birds{2}, by My leave, then breathe into it so it becomes birds{3}, by My leave; and when you heal the born-blind and the leper, by My leave; and when you bring out the dead, by My leave; and when I restrained the Children of Israel from you when you brought them the evident proofs. But those who denied among them said, `This is nothing but evident sorcery{4}.’”",1:[A grammatical shift from past tense to present tense.],2:[Qira’at: Abu Ja’far read it as: “…the shape of a bird,”],3:[Qira’at: Nafie’, Abu Ja’far and Ya’qub read it as: “…so it becomes a bird,”],4:[Qira’at: Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “…an evident sorcerer.”]
  5,111,"And recall when I revealed to the disciples: “Believe in Me and in My Messenger.” They said, “We have attained faith, so bear witness that We are certainly Muslims{1}.”",1:[The Arabic word used is Muslimoonwhich means those who willingly submit to God, regardless of which prophet they followed.]
  5,112,"And recall when the disciples said, “O Jesus, son of Mary, can{1}yourLord bestow upon us from on high{2}a table spread<i>(with food) </i>from heaven?” He said, “Be mindful of Allah, if you are believers.”",1:[Qira’at: Al-Kesa’i read it as: “…can you (ask) your to Lord…”],2:[Qira’at: Ibn Kathir, Abu Amr and Ya’qub read it as: “… can your Lord send down to us…”]
  5,113,"They said, “We want to eat from it, and so that our hearts are serene, and to know that you have told us the truth, and to be of its witnesses.”"
